-- DER BIERGARTEN -- World Cup 2026 Ground Zero
-- ============================================================
UPDATE bars SET content = '<h3>The Vibe</h3>
<p>Der Biergarten is Atlanta''s soccer headquarters, and it knows it. The moment you step inside this 7,000-square-foot German beer garden on Marietta Street, you understand why it has been the spiritual home of Atlanta United supporters since the club launched in 2017. Rustic brick walls, warm wood accents, string lights over the elevated outdoor patio, and the sound of German beer steins clinking set the stage. On match days, this place transforms from a refined beer garden into a roaring supporters'' den.</p>

<h3>The Setup</h3>
<p>The indoor space includes an elegant dining room, a games alley with Fussball tables and table shuffleboard, and the signature indoor/outdoor beer garden. Multiple large screens are positioned throughout, with dedicated audio for the main match. The outdoor patio is the real draw on nice days, offering an open-air atmosphere that makes watching a daytime kickoff feel like being at a European fan zone. Der Biergarten is steps from Mercedes-Benz Stadium, the Georgia Aquarium, and CNN Center.</p>

<h3>World Cup 2026</h3>
<p>Atlanta is a host city for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, with matches at Mercedes-Benz Stadium. Der Biergarten''s location makes it arguably the most important pre-match and watch-party venue in the city. It sits within walking distance of the stadium, and its German beer garden identity is tailor-made for World Cup culture. The team has already begun planning expanded viewing events for the tournament, with outdoor projections and extended capacity during match days.</p>

<h3>Food and Drink</h3>
<p>This is a proper German beer garden with premium German beers on tap, served in authentic steins. The food menu features traditional German cuisine -- bratwurst, schnitzel, pretzels with beer cheese, and currywurst alongside more familiar pub fare. The combination of cold German beer and match-day tension is something special. A cocktail program and wine list round out the offerings for non-beer drinkers.</p>

<h3>Atlanta United Connection</h3>
<p>As an official Atlanta United Pub Partner, Der Biergarten hosts watch parties for every match with ticket giveaways, special events, and promotional activations. Pre-match crowds heading to Mercedes-Benz Stadium for Five Stripes home games often start here, and the energy carries right into the stadium. It has been a consistent destination for Atlanta''s soccer community since the club''s founding season.</p>

<h3>Insider Tips</h3>
<p>Arrive early for any Atlanta United home match or major international fixture. The patio fills fast. During World Cup 2026, this will be one of the most popular gathering spots in the city, so plan accordingly. The Fussball tables in the back alley are a great way to kill time before kickoff.</p>'
WHERE slug = 'der-biergarten-atlanta';

