-- THE MIDWAY PUB -- Footie Mob Headquarters
-- ============================================================
UPDATE bars SET content = '<h3>The Vibe</h3>
<p>The Midway Pub is not just a bar that shows soccer -- it is the home of Footie Mob, one of Atlanta United''s original and most passionate independent supporter groups. On away match days, the scene at 552 Flat Shoals Ave is intense: flags draped from the ceiling, scarves around every neck, and chants that carry out to the street. This is East Atlanta Village at its most authentic -- a neighborhood pub where the regulars know each other by name and the soccer community is the beating heart of the place.</p>

<h3>The Setup</h3>
<p>The interior is a no-frills East Atlanta Village classic: dark wood, a long bar, big-screen TVs positioned for sightlines from every seat, and a projector for the main event. The real star is the massive outdoor patio, one of the biggest in the neighborhood, which is dog-friendly and kid-friendly during the day. When the weather cooperates, the patio becomes an open-air stadium of sorts, with fans spilling out with beers and plates of food.</p>

<h3>The Footie Mob</h3>
<p>Footie Mob predates Atlanta United''s on-field debut, having formed as one of the founding independent supporter groups. They have made The Midway their home turf, and every away match is an event. The energy mirrors what you would find in the supporter sections at Mercedes-Benz Stadium -- synchronized chants, tifo displays, and a level of passion that sets this apart from a typical sports bar. If you want to understand Atlanta''s soccer culture at the grassroots level, this is where you come.</p>

<h3>Food and Drink</h3>
<p>The menu is unpretentious pub fare done well. The garlic pretzels are a local favorite, the chicken fingers are legitimately great, and the burger holds its own against fancier options elsewhere in the neighborhood. The beer selection is huge, tilting toward craft, and prices are fair for the area. For morning Premier League matches, the kitchen opens early with a more limited menu.</p>

<h3>Who Goes There</h3>
<p>The crowd is a mix of die-hard Footie Mob members, East Atlanta Village locals, and soccer fans from around the city who know that this is where the atmosphere lives. It is not a corporate sports bar -- it is a neighborhood pub that happens to have one of the most passionate soccer communities in the American South. EPL mornings draw a smaller but dedicated crowd, while Atlanta United away matches pack the house.</p>

<h3>Getting There</h3>
<p>The Midway is in the heart of East Atlanta Village at the intersection of Flat Shoals and Glenwood. Street parking is available on surrounding blocks. Rideshare is recommended for match days when the lot fills up. It is about a 10-minute drive from Mercedes-Benz Stadium.</p>'
WHERE slug = 'the-midway-pub-atlanta';

