-- MANNY'S GRANT PARK -- Atlanta Spurs (Tottenham) Home
-- ============================================================
UPDATE bars SET content = '<h3>The Vibe</h3>
<p>Manny''s Grant Park is the kind of neighborhood pub where you walk in as a stranger and leave knowing everyone at the bar. Located at 580 Woodward Ave in the heart of Grant Park, it has carved out a specific identity in Atlanta''s soccer landscape as the official home of the Atlanta Spurs, Tottenham Hotspur''s recognized supporters'' club. On match days, the pub takes on the feel of a mini-stadium, with Spurs fans in Lilywhite kits crowding around the screens, reacting to every tackle and near-miss in real time.</p>

<h3>The Spurs Connection</h3>
<p>The Atlanta Spurs supporters'' club was founded in 2012 and has grown steadily ever since. They chose Manny''s as their home bar because of the staff''s fantastic hospitality and the pub''s willingness to make match day a genuine event. Anytime Spurs are playing, you are guaranteed to find like-minded fans raising a glass together. The partnership between the club and the pub has been instrumental in creating a community that extends beyond just watching football -- it is a social hub for Tottenham fans across the metro area.</p>

<h3>The Setup</h3>
<p>Manny''s is not a massive sports bar with 50 screens. It is a cozy neighborhood pub with enough TVs to cover the matches that matter, and the atmosphere more than compensates for the intimate size. The bar area is the focal point on match days, with fans standing shoulder to shoulder. A spacious patio out back provides overflow seating on nice days, and the whole place has a warm, unpretentious feel that suits the Grant Park neighborhood perfectly.</p>

<h3>Food and Drink</h3>
<p>Quality pub food is the focus -- burgers, wings, and comfort fare that pairs well with a pint. The drink selection leans toward craft beers and classic cocktails. Nothing too fancy, nothing overpriced. It is the kind of place where you order without agonizing over the menu and are never disappointed.</p>

<h3>The Neighborhood</h3>
<p>Grant Park is one of Atlanta''s oldest and most charming neighborhoods, and Manny''s fits right in. It is conveniently located off I-20, near Oakland Cemetery and the Eastside Beltline, and less than a mile from the MLK MARTA stop. There is a small parking lot behind the pub plus ample free street parking on the surrounding blocks. The neighborhood is walkable, bikeable, and an easy rideshare from anywhere in the city.</p>

<h3>Beyond Spurs</h3>
<p>While the Tottenham connection is the headline, Manny''s is a good soccer pub in general. The staff will put on any match you want to watch, and the crowd is friendly to fans of all clubs. It is also just a great neighborhood bar for any occasion -- trivia nights, weekend brunch, or a casual weeknight pint. The Spurs identity gives it a specific character, but the hospitality extends to everyone.</p>'
WHERE slug = 'mannys-grant-park-atlanta';

